{"id":"1302.6131","submitter":"Sylwia Cichacz","authors":"Sylwia Cichacz","title":"Note on group distance magic complete bipartite graphs","comments":"Since the politc of the Journal I submitted the paper I need to\n  withdraw the paper from arxiv","journal-ref":"Central European Journal of Mathematics 12(3) (2014) 529-533","doi":"10.2478/s11533-013-0356-z","report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A $\\Gamma$-distance magic labeling of a graph $G=(V,E)$ with $|V | = n$ is a\nbijection $\\ell$ from $V$ to an Abelian group $\\Gamma$ of order $n$ such that\nthe weight $w(x)=\\sum_{y\\in N_G(x)}\\ell(y)$ of every vertex $x \\in V$ is equal\nto the same element $\\mu \\in \\Gamma$, called the \\emph{magic constant}. A graph\n$G$ is called a \\emph{group distance magic graph} if there exists a $\\Gamma\n$-distance magic labeling for every Abelian group $\\Gamma$ of order $|V(G)|$.\n  In this paper we prove that some complete $k$-partite graphs are\n$\\mathbb{Z}_p$-distance magic. Moreover we prove that $K_{m,n}$ is a group\ndistance magic if and only if $n+m \\not \\equiv 2 \\pmod 4$. We also show that if\n$n+m \\equiv 2 \\pmod 4$, then there does not exist a group $\\Gamma$ of order\n$n+m$ such that there exists a $\\Gamma$-distance labeling for $K_{m,n}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Feb 2013 15:52:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 10 Mar 2013 20:32:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-04"}
